**RE: Division of Labeling Review Decision — ****[Drug Name]**** (ANDA ****[ANDA No.]****)**

Dear **[Applicant POC]**,

The Division of Labeling Review (DLR) has completed its review of the proposed labeling submitted for **[Drug Name]** under Abbreviated New Drug Application (ANDA) No. **[ANDA No.]**. This letter communicates the DLR's labeling review decision and any actions required on your part.

**LABELING REVIEW DECISION**

Decision: **[FDA Labeling Decision]**     |     DLR Reviewer: **[DLR POC]**

**Acceptable: **No labeling deficiencies were identified. The proposed labeling is found to be acceptable as submitted. No further labeling-related action is required at this time.

**Acceptable with Minor Deficiencies: **The proposed labeling is provisionally acceptable; however, minor deficiencies have been identified that must be resolved prior to final approval. Please submit corrected labeling addressing the items listed in Attachment A within **30 calendar days** of the date of this letter.

**Acceptable with Major Deficiencies: **The proposed labeling contains major deficiencies that must be corrected. Please submit a complete revised labeling package addressing all items in Attachment A within **60 calendar days** of the date of this letter. Failure to respond within this timeframe may result in a refuse-to-file action.

**Not Acceptable: **The proposed labeling is not acceptable. The deficiencies identified are of a nature that require a comprehensive labeling revision. A full response to all items detailed in Attachment A must be submitted within **90 calendar days** of this letter. You may request a Type B meeting with DLR to discuss the deficiencies.

**ATTACHMENT A — LABELING DEFICIENCIES**

(Complete for Acceptable-Minor, Acceptable-Major, and Not Acceptable decisions only)

*[List deficiencies here, e.g.: 1. Section X — revise wording per 21 CFR § XX.XX ...]*

**REQUIRED RESPONSE / NEXT STEPS**

Please submit all labeling responses via the FDA Electronic Submissions Gateway (ESG) referencing ANDA No. **[ANDA No.]**. Direct any questions regarding this review to the DLR Reviewer of Record listed above.

